<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>Effective ways to use pass-along cards include:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Hand them to prospective students:</strong> As you interact with prospective students at presentations, firesides, or elsewhere -- hand out pass-along cards. This will serve as a reminder and direct individuals to apply.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Give them to current students:</strong> Current Pathway students are one of the most effective ways to bring new students into the program. Always have some cards handy at your gatherings each week to hand out to any of your students who would like some.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Use them like a business card: </strong>The back side of the pass-along card has some empty space where you could write in your contact information, or even print off a small label.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><strong>Provide them to local leaders &amp; Institutes</strong>: Give a few cards to your local Institute and ask them to set them out. Also give a few (5-10 cards) to local priesthood leaders so they can hand them to students they'd like to refer.</li>
</ul>
<h3>How to Get Them</h3>
<p>You can request pass-along cards by filling out the&nbsp;<a href="https://byui.az1.qualtrics.com/SE/?SID=SV_3DdiYTyklN5Wt0x">Missionary Marketing Order Form</a>.</p>
